#What is SparkSQL and DataFrames?
## SparkSQL: It's a Spark module for structured data processing that provides a data abstraction called DataFrames and acts as a distributed SQL query engine 
## DataFrame: It's a distributed collection of data organized into named columns.

## Read from Json files

/** Read Data from a Json file and then
* Use "show" function to display the contents of the DataFrame */
val peopleDF = sqlContext.read.json("/home/emaasit/Desktop/Apache/incubator-zeppelin-master/data/people.json")
peopleDF.show()

%md
## DataFrame Operations
### DataFrames allow for structured data manipulation

result.msg:
DataFrame Operations

DataFrames allow for structured data manipulation

paragraphs.text:
/** Print the schema of the DF in a tree format */
peopleDF.printSchema()

result.msg:
root
 |-- age: long (nullable = true)
 |-- name: string (nullable = true)

paragraphs.text:
/** Select only one column */
peopleDF.select("name").show()

/** Select only people older than 21 */
peopleDF.filter("age > 21").show()

/** Use "groupBy" and "count" functions to count people in age groups */
peopleDF.groupBy("age").count().show()

%md
## Running SQL queries Programmatically

/** Use the "sql" function "sqlContext" to run SQL queries */
peopleDF.registerTempTable("peopleTable")
val adultsDF = sqlContext.sql("select * from peopleTable where age > 21")
adultsDF.show()

## Data Sources

### 1. Parquet Files

/** Option 1: Reading data while specifying the data format */
val parquetDF = sqlContext.read.format("parquet").load("/home/emaasit/Desktop/Apache/incubator-zeppelin-master/data/users.parquet")

### 2. Json Files

option("header", "true").
option("inferSchema", "true").
load("/home/emaasit/Desktop/Apache/incubator-zeppelin-master/data/flights.csv")

flightsDF.registerTempTable("flightsTable")
